---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import RuleCard from '../../../../components/RuleCard.astro';
import { getRulesByCategory, ruleCategories } from '../../../../data/rules';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Rules Overview | Blueprint Health Analyzer"
  description="Complete list of all 13 rules in Blueprint Health Analyzer with severity levels and brief descriptions."
>
  <h1>Rules Overview</h1>

  <p>
    Blueprint Health Analyzer currently ships with 13 built-in rules across Blueprint, Material,
    Asset, Niagara, and Rendering categories. Full visual write-ups are being added rule by rule;
    until then, each rule page still resolves and shows its current scope and documentation status.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-callout">
    <strong>Current Phase 2 status:</strong> navigation, placeholder routes, and shared rule
    components are wired. Full rule content is Phase 3 work.
  </div>

  {ruleCategories.map((category) => {
    const rules = getRulesByCategory(category);

    return (
      <>
        <h2>{category} Rules</h2>
        <div class="docs-grid">
          {rules.map((rule) => (
            <RuleCard rule={rule} />
          ))}
        </div>
      </>
    );
  })}

  <h2>Severity Levels</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Critical</strong>: Likely to cause noticeable performance, memory, or shipping-risk issues.</li>
    <li><strong>Warning</strong>: Needs review because it can become expensive or hard to maintain at scale.</li>
    <li><strong>Info</strong>: Context worth checking, but not usually a blocker.</li>
    <li><strong>Suggestion</strong>: Best-practice improvement with lower immediate risk.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Configuration Status</h2>
  <p>
    Today, the plugin exposes threshold and scan-scope configuration. Per-rule enable/disable,
    severity overrides, and persistent allowlists are planned v1.1 work, not shipped behavior yet.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
